[[File:Light_amplification_goggles.jpg|250px|thumb|A pair of the goggles]]
'''Light amplification goggles''', also known as '''infra-goggles''', were a type of [[Goggles/Legends|goggles]] similar to [[Macrobinoculars/Legends|macrobinoculars]]. The difference is that these goggles could filter and balance levels of light, allowing the user to see in pitch black areas, though the vision was cast in a greenish hue. The infra-goggles required batteries to function, which drained at a rate comparative to [[Electrobinoculars/Legends|Electrobinoculars]]. They could be worn during combat, which came to good use when [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Kyle Katarn]] used them in the dark mines of [[Artus Prime]].<ref name="JKIIJO">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]''</ref>

